<task id="007" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-07 Add `AvailableInContexts` Enum + Dataverse Column to `AnalysisTool` DTO (Pillar 2)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed>2026-06-07</completed>
    <completion-notes>
      DTO: Added `ToolAvailabilityContext` enum (Playbook=100000000, Chat=100000001, Both=100000002 — Spaarke canonical option-set values) + nullable `AvailableInContexts` property on `AnalysisTool` record in `IScopeResolverService.cs`. Plain enum (NOT [Flags]) — Dataverse single-select picklist semantics require explicit `Both` value.

      Dataverse: Deployed `sprk_availableincontexts` option-set column to existing `sprk_analysistool` entity via new idempotent script `scripts/Add-AnalysisToolAvailableInContexts.ps1` (modeled on `Create-AiPersonaEntity.ps1`). DefaultFormValue=100000000 preserves Playbook behavior for all pre-R6 rows. Customizations published. Idempotency verified by post-deploy dry-run.

      Service mapper: `AnalysisToolService.MapAvailableInContexts(int?)` converts raw Dataverse values to enum (null → null at DTO; null → Playbook semantics applied at downstream resolve time per FR-07 backward-compat). Updated `ToolEntity` JSON property + OData $select clause + 3 AnalysisTool construction sites (Get/List/Create).

      Tests: 18 new tests in `AnalysisToolDtoTests.cs` cover enum value contract, default DTO state, round-trip JSON serialization for all 3 values + null, mapper for known/unknown/null raw values, record `with` expression preserves field. All 18 pass; full BFF unit suite 6141 pass / 0 fail.

      Build: green (0 errors, 0 warnings). Publish-size delta: 0.00 MB compressed (baseline 45.5 → post 45.5; well within ≤+5 MB R6 budget and 60 MB hard ceiling).

      ADR compliance: ADR-010 (zero DI changes), ADR-013 (no PublicContracts modifications), ADR-027 (sprk_ prefix + unmanaged), ADR-029 (delta verified). FR-07 backward-compat invariant honored. No new feature flags, no Agent Framework refs.

      Decisions: (1) Plain enum vs Flags — chose plain because Dataverse single-select picklist + explicit Both value (FR-07 enumerates 3 values, not bit combinations). (2) Nullable DTO field — explicit nullable for migration safety; mapper preserves null and treats null-as-Playbook semantics at downstream resolve sites (per FR-07). (3) Field placed directly in AnalysisTool record (no separate Models/Ai/ file split) — record is already authoritative + co-located with related Tool* types in IScopeResolverService.cs; keeps task 008 (JsonSchema add) trivial without forcing a partial-class split.

      Task 008 ready to proceed: same DTO + entity surface; pattern established (PicklistAttributeMetadata for option-set columns; this task can be MemoAttributeMetadata for JsonSchema string).
    </completion-notes>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>006</dependencies>
    <blocks>010</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, dataverse, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Schema change to production `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse entity (Confirmation Trigger) + `.cs` DTO modification + downstream blocker.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential with 008 (both modify `AnalysisTool` DTO and `sprk_analysistool` entity). Run 007 then 008.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add `AvailableInContexts` enum (`Playbook` / `Chat` / `Both`) discriminator field to
    the `AnalysisTool` DTO + a corresponding Dataverse column on `sprk_analysistool`.
    Existing playbook tool rows default to `Playbook` (backward-compat). New chat tools
    declare `Chat` or `Both` to expose themselves to `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools()`
    in task 011.

    Critical-path context: this discriminator is how the chat-agent's data-driven tool
    list is filtered. Tasks 010 (adapter) reads the field, task 011 (factory) filters by
    `AvailableInContexts ∋ "Chat"`, and task 012 (batch migration of 10 chat tools) sets
    this field on the new `sprk_analysistool` rows.

    The Dataverse column is an option-set (1=Playbook, 2=Chat, 3=Both); default = 1
    (Playbook). DTO field is the matching C# enum + nullable for migration safety.
    Schema change to production entity requires Confirmation Trigger pause.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with experience modifying `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse entity and
    the corresponding `AnalysisTool` DTO. Familiar with option-set columns and DTO
    backward-compat patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `AnalysisTool` DTO has `AvailableInContexts` enum field; `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse
    entity has the matching option-set column with `Playbook` default. Existing tool rows
    preserve their behavior (default to `Playbook`). Unit tests cover enum
    serialization/deserialization. Build green; publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

